      • partArray

        public static byte[] partArray(byte[] srcArray,
                               int outputArraySize)
                        throws OutputArraySizeTooLargeException
        Copies a srcArray, but only the first bytes until outputArraySize.
        Parameters:
        srcArray - the array you want to copy from
        outputArraySize - the size you want the output array to be. Or the amount of bytes you want to copy from the src array to the output array minus 1
        Returns:
        An array that contains the data of the srcArray, but only containing outputArraySize bytes
        Throws:
        OutputArraySizeTooLargeException - when the outputArraySize is bigger than the srcArray's length

      • partArray

        public static byte[] partArray(byte[] srcArray,
                               int outputArraySize,
                               int srcArrayStartingPosition)
                        throws OutputArraySizeTooLargeException
        Copies a srcArray, but only the first bytes until outputArraySize.
        Parameters:
        srcArray - the array you want to copy from
        outputArraySize - the size you want the output array to be. Or the amount of bytes you want to copy from the src array to the output array minus 1
        srcArrayStartingPosition - the offset where the method will start copying the srcArray
        Returns:
        An array that contains the data of the srcArray, but only containing outputArraySize bytes
        Throws:
        OutputArraySizeTooLargeException - when the outputArraySize is bigger than the srcArray's length - srcArrayStartingPosition
